\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line Stenden South Africa BV \'28Incorporated in the Netherlands\'29\'2C previous known as  Educational Institute for\line Service Studies International \'28Pty\'29 Ltd.\'2C is a registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training as a private higher education provider and is accredited to offer only a Bachelor of Commerce \'28Hospitality Management\'29.\line An application was made for a Bachelor of Business Administration in Disaster Relief Management that served before the Accreditation Committee Meeting of 01 June2011. It was recommended that the decision be deferred for the following reasons\'3A\line 1. The institution needed to clarify in detail the level and composition of the programme. The research \'28dissertation\'29 and practical component \'28internship\'29 comprising 120 credits appear to be at a level not relevant to a BBA degree and more detail is required on the programme design and level of modules. For example\'2C there is a need to clarify why experiential learning is not spread to all levels.\line 2. The institution needs to provide in more detail where students will be doing their experiential training as well as the nature of the work-based learning and the assessment thereof.\line 3. The institution is required to provide evidence through a workload allocation model the academic staff that will be teaching on the programme in terms of the relevance of their qualifications and experience.\line \line The institution has submitted all the additional information requested and this information has been evaluated.\line \cell \pard 

\intbl \row \pard 
\line \par\pard\trowd\trqc \trpaddl113\trpaddt113\trpaddb113\trpaddr113\trpaddfl3\trpaddft3\trpaddfb3\trpaddfr3\trgaph100\trrh100\trleft36
