\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator\'27s report indicates that criteria 2\'2C 3 \'2C 4\'2C 6 and 7 meet the minimum requirements and criteria 1 and 5 need further improvement. \line \line It has been indicated that although an initial concern was expressed over the large research component\'2C the partial compliance in the submission of this document \'28supporting the experiential training component\'29 is considered acceptable. It must however be stated that although the LOCAL SANDF unit has given written submission of support\'2C this must still be ratified and substantiated by the higher echelons of the SANDF \'28head office\'29. Until such time that a formal agreement or arrangement \'28contract\'29 with the SANDF at head office level is submitted this criterion is still in need of improvement. \line \line According to the curriculum the course entails other experiential training for which no evidence of possible contracts is presented. These sets of evidence of experiential training facilities will need to be contracted and presented in evidence. This absence of proof will be considered as a long-term condition.\line \line Information provided regarding the work load allocation and qualification of staff members is sufficient.\line \line The level of the qualification\'2C that is\'2C whether a BBA is a level 8 qualification needs to be considered.\line \line \cell \pard 

